                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720715-60-off305 t17720715-60-crimeloc308"></join>; I lost eight bobbins of silk on the 19th of June. Acton and the prisoner Sheffield worked with me; Acton came up, and said a man came to call on Sheffield that he did not like, and begged I would take notice of him; they went out together. I then examined the silk and missed eight bobbins; Sheffield staid out all night; he came to work at six o'clock next morning. I got a warrant from Sir 
